node.text: Was such a pleasure to join @drmarkhyman along with @keeoone on The Doctor’s Farmacy to talk about my realisation that cutting out sugar and using food as medicine is the key to feeling good. The answers aren’t in pills, they’re on your plate. The smallest of choices we make every day, like the food we choose to eat from our plates, makes a huge difference in our long term health.

node.text: 🍉WATERMELON🍉- Lots of people are afraid of buying watermelon, me included until @laurahopperhops showed me how to cut up! It’s so easy to do, and it’s a great snack to have in the fridge for a small cost if you buy them whole! Super high in vitamin C and lower in sugar than a lot of fruits! Put in to a container  or bowl covered in bees wrap or a BPA free container, it can be waaaay cheaper than buying it already chopped in wasteful plastic, and you make it last around a week for snacking! Boom! Enjoy! Kids will love it too
So proud of my amazing wife @laurahopperhops talking about this. It’s been a huge struggle, at times, in our marriage. But, as always, she’s a warrior and is winning the battle against anxiety. ❤️

Sweet tooth craving -guilt free and actually healthy alternative.

Anti inflammatory Turmeric- get it without tasting it!

@myviome - here’s what it is!

Monkfruit explained! @lakanto @buddhafruit 
How to make healthy foods you think are bland and tasteless a little more exciting, but won’t pack on the pounds like a sugary store bought sauce!
Big up @hunterandgatheruk
@primalkitchenfoods
